---
const docsUrl = 'https://docs.getordo.dev';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Ordo</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Self-hosted, declarative infrastructure management for stateful machines."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<header>
			<a href="/" class="brand">Ordo</a>
			<nav>
				<a href="#install">Install</a>
					<a href="#schemas">Schemas</a>
					<a href={docsUrl}>Docs</a>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main>
			<section class="hero">
				<h1>Ordo</h1>
				<p class="tagline">
					Intentional infrastructure — define state, detect drift, act
					deliberately.
				</p>
				<p>
					<a class="cta" href={docsUrl}>Read the docs</a>
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>The problem</h2>
				<p>
					Existing tools for managing stateful machines are either too
					big to operate or too small to trust.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>What Ordo does</h2>
				<p>
					Declarative state management, drift detection, progressive
					deployment, and an audit trail — all self-hosted by default.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Who it is for</h2>
				<p>
					Teams running real workloads on machines they own.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Architecture at a glance</h2>
				<p>
					An orchestrator on one machine; agents on the rest.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section id="install">
				<h2>Install</h2>
				<p>
					Each component installs on the machine that runs it. On Linux
					and macOS:
				</p>

				<p>
					<strong>Operator / client tools</strong> — your workstation
					(installs <code>ordo</code> and <code>ordo-state</code>):
				</p>
				<pre
					class="install"><code>curl -fsSL https://getordo.dev/install.sh | sh</code></pre>

				<p><strong>Orchestrator</strong> — the control host:</p>
				<pre
					class="install"><code>curl -fsSL https://getordo.dev/install.sh | sh -s -- ordo-orchestrator</code></pre>

				<p><strong>Agent</strong> — each managed machine:</p>
				<pre
					class="install"><code>curl -fsSL https://getordo.dev/install.sh | sh -s -- ordo-agent</code></pre>

				<p class="muted">
					On Windows, <code>irm https://getordo.dev/install.ps1 | iex</code
					> installs the client tools. The installer downloads a prebuilt
					binary from <code>dl.getordo.dev</code>,
					verifies its SHA-256 checksum, and checks the <a
						href="/minisign.pub">minisign signature</a
					> when minisign is installed. Debian and RPM packages are
					published alongside the archives in the same release.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section id="schemas">
				<h2>Editor schemas</h2>
				<p>
					Machine-readable JSON Schemas for Ordo's module and
					configuration files — point your editor at them for
					autocompletion and validation:
				</p>
				<ul class="schemas">
					<li>
						Module files —
						<code>https://getordo.dev/schemas/module/v1.json</code>
					</li>
					<li>
						Orchestrator config —
						<code
							>https://getordo.dev/schemas/orchestrator-config/v1.json</code
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						Agent config —
						<code>https://getordo.dev/schemas/agent-config/v1.json</code
						>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p>In a module file, add a modeline:</p>
				<pre
					class="install"><code># yaml-language-server: $schema=https://getordo.dev/schemas/module/v1.json</code></pre>
				<p class="muted">
					See the <a href={`${docsUrl}/reference/`}>reference docs</a> for
					VS Code and JetBrains setup.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer>
			<p>Ephyra Software</p>
		</footer>

		<style is:global>
			:root {
				color-scheme: light;
				--text: #1a1a1a;
				--muted: #5a5a5a;
				--accent: #1a1a1a;
				--rule: #e5e5e5;
			}
			html {
				font-family:
					ui-serif, Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
				color: var(--text);
				background: #fafaf7;
			}
			body {
				margin: 0;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}
			header,
			main,
			footer {
				max-width: 42rem;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 0 1.5rem;
			}
			header {
				display: flex;
				justify-content: space-between;
				align-items: baseline;
				padding-top: 1.5rem;
				padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
			}
			.brand {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				font-weight: 600;
				color: var(--text);
				text-decoration: none;
				letter-spacing: 0.02em;
			}
			nav a {
				color: var(--muted);
				text-decoration: none;
			}
			nav a:hover {
				color: var(--text);
			}
			main {
				padding-top: 3rem;
				padding-bottom: 3rem;
			}
			section {
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}
			.hero {
				margin-bottom: 4rem;
			}
			.hero h1 {
				font-size: 2.5rem;
				margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
			}
			.tagline {
				color: var(--muted);
				font-size: 1.15rem;
				margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
			}
			h2 {
				font-size: 1.15rem;
				margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
			}
			p {
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
			}
			.cta {
				display: inline-block;
				color: #fafaf7;
				background: var(--accent);
				padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
				text-decoration: none;
				border-radius: 2px;
			}
			.cta:hover {
				background: #333;
			}
			.install {
				font-family: ui-monospace, 'SFMono-Regular', Menlo, Consolas,
					monospace;
				font-size: 0.9rem;
				background: #f0efe9;
				border: 1px solid var(--rule);
				border-radius: 2px;
				padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
				overflow-x: auto;
			}
			.muted {
				color: var(--muted);
				font-size: 0.95rem;
			}
			.schemas {
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
				padding-left: 1.25rem;
			}
			.schemas li {
				margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
			}
			.schemas code,
			.install code {
				word-break: break-all;
			}
			footer {
				border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
				padding-top: 1.5rem;
				padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
				color: var(--muted);
				font-size: 0.9rem;
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
